#: ../../source/matching.rst:3
msgid "Matching Circuits"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/matching.rst:6
msgid "Creating matching circuits is an often needed task in microwave technology. "
"Qucs can do this automatically. These are the neccessary steps:"
msgstr "Criar circuitos de casamento é uma tarefa frequentemente necessária na "
"tecnologia de microondas. Qucs pode fazer isso automaticamente. Estes são os "
"passos necessarios:"

#: ../../source/matching.rst:10
msgid "Perform an S-parameter simulation in order to calculate the reflexion "
"coefficient."
msgstr "Faça uma simulação de parâmetro-S para calcular o coeficiente de reflexão."

#: ../../source/matching.rst:13
msgid "Place a diagram and display the reflexion coefficient (i.e. S[1,1] for port "
"1, S[2,2] for port 2 etc.)"
msgstr "Coloque um diagrama e exiba o coeficiente de reflexão (ex. S[1,1] para port "
"1, S[2,2] para port 2 etc.)"

#: ../../source/matching.rst:16
msgid "Set a marker on the graph and step to the desired frequency."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/matching.rst:18
msgid "Click with the right mouse button on the marker and select \"power "
"matching\" in the appearing menu."
msgstr "Clique com o botão direito do mouse no marcador e selecione no menu que "
"aparecer a opção \"casamento de potência\"."

#: ../../source/matching.rst:21
msgid "A dialog appears where the values can be adjusted, for example the reference"
" impedance can be chosen different from 50 ohms."
msgstr "Uma janela aparecerá onde os valores podem ser ajustados, por exemplo: A "
"impedância de referência pode ser escolhida diferente dos 50 ohms."

#: ../../source/matching.rst:24
msgid "After clicking \"create\" the page switches back to the schematic and by "
"moving the mouse cursor the matching circuit can be placed."
msgstr "Após clicar em \"criar\" a página retornará para o esquema elétrico e "
"movendo o cursor do mouse, o circuito de casamento poderá ser colocado."

#: ../../source/matching.rst:30
msgid "The left-hand side of the matching circuit is the input and the right-hand "
"side must be connected to the circuit."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/matching.rst:33
msgid "If the marker points to a variable called \"Sopt\", the menu shows the "
"option \"noise matching\". Note that the only different to \"power "
"matching\" is the fact that the conjugate complex reflexion coefficient is "
"taken. So if the variable has another name, noise matching can be chosen by "
"re-adjusting the values in the dialog."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/matching.rst:39
msgid "The matching dialog can also be called by menu (Tools->matching circuit) or "
"by short-cut (<CTRL-5>). But then all values has to be entered manually."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/matching.rst:44
msgid "2-Port Matching Circuits"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/matching.rst:47
msgid ""
"If the variable name in the marker text is an S-parameter, then an option "
"exists for concurrently matching input and output of a two-port circuit. "
"This works quite alike the above-mentioned steps. It results in two "
"L-circuits: The very left node is for connecting port 1, the very right node"
" is for connectiong port 2 and the two node in the middle are for connecting"
" the two-port circuit."
msgstr ""

